# TypeScript Conventions

- Strict mode, no `any` — use `unknown` with narrowing
- No semicolons, single quotes
- All shared interfaces centralized in `src/types/index.ts`
- Discriminated unions via `type` field for variant data (see `ContentBlock`)
- Custom hooks: named export, return `{ data, loading, error }` pattern
- Type assertions: prefer `as Promise<Type>` on `.json()` calls over generic parameters
- Module-level caching (plain objects) over React state for cross-component data sharing
